Sanitize Seurat Markers

Source: R/SeuratMarkers.R
SeuratMarkers.Rd

This generator function is designed to take the original return from a Seurat marker analysis and add corresponding gene annotations.

SeuratMarkers(markers, ranges, alpha = 0.05)

Arguments

markers

data.frame. Unmodified Seurat::FindAllMarkers() or Seurat::FindMarkers() return.
ranges

GRanges. Gene annotations. Names must correspond to the rownames defined in seurat@data. The function will automatically subset the ranges and arrange them alphabetically.
alpha

scalar numeric. Alpha cutoff (adjusted P value; false discovery rate).

Value

SeuratMarkers. Results are arranged by adjusted P value, and grouped per cluster if applicable.

Note

Seurat::FindAllMarkers() maps the counts matrix rownames correctly in the gene column, whereas Seurat::FindMarkers() maps them correctly in the rownames of the returned marker data.frame.

Examples

data(seurat_small)
object <- seurat_small

## `FindAllMarkers()` return.
invisible(capture.output(
    all_markers <- Seurat::FindAllMarkers(object)
))
all_sanitized <- SeuratMarkers(
    markers = all_markers,
    ranges = rowRanges(object)
)
